entry.title: Covid-19 Shots Risk Displacing Immunizations Against Childhood Killers in Developing Countries
entry.content: As underfunded healthcare systems shift to immunizing adults against Covid, 2022 risks seeing further setbacks in the fight against some of the leading killers of young children in developing countries.

entry.title: U.S. Businesses Sour on Saudi Arabia in Blow to Crown Prince
entry.content: Surprise tax hits, unpaid bills and stolen intellectual property are undoing the government’s effort to shift the kingdom’s economy away from oil.
